l diaries during times of heated conflict and bloodshed. Extensive notes and a short chronology assist the interested reader and scholar in disentangling the complicated plot. After years of relative political passivity, Mesic was elected independent Croatia's second president in 2000, following the death of former President Franjo Tudman.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aYugoslav War, 1991-1995zCroatia. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aLate 20th century, Personal narratives, Political studies, Yugoslav War.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998z978311078055040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978615505387040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9786155053870423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9786155053870/original  a978-3-11-078055-0  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998c1998d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK